{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/delete-gh-repo/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Abel L. Mbula"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3d439bf5-1f60-5d76-88af-ecf669526fb5","excerpt":"When learning Git and GitHub, you create so many repos just for a test. Once you master the skill, you no longer need those repos. So, how do you delete them…","html":"<p>When learning Git and GitHub, you create so many repos just for a test. Once you master the skill, you no longer need those repos. So, how do you delete them? This post is there to answer to your question.</p>\n<p>Let’s go step by step!</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Login to <a href=\"https://github.com/\">Github</a></li>\n<li>Open the repo you want to delete</li>\n<li>Click Setting tab (the last on the right)</li>\n<li>Scroll down till the <code class=\"language-text\">Danger zone</code> (you have read well, Danger zone) </li>\n<li>Click <code class=\"language-text\">Delete this repository</code> (once done, you cannot revert the operation, so think twice before hitting thr button)</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/872c00cd4df59382238edfddf5c08859/55cb2/del-gh-repo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 13.197278911564625%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAiElEQVQI102Niw6DIAxF/f/PXAZsKohoFORxJjiXNTm5t21u20mleAqBkJKUEjln8q1f3+YpNy2lUKv6bZzYBsNu7KVupZPqxc2oNcZa7OzQxjCMV1/9ZOe2j+ehWvF85mTPIt4sqsc9JKu2dMUHCAclBPLuf6Rtb/zPGt5TMy0X40m6tD46Ih/P9ugpCIL7CAAAAABJRU5ErkJggg=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Danger zone\"\n        title=\"Danger zone\"\n        src=\"/static/872c00cd4df59382238edfddf5c08859/799d3/del-gh-repo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/872c00cd4df59382238edfddf5c08859/00d96/del-gh-repo.png 148w,\n/static/872c00cd4df59382238edfddf5c08859/0b23c/del-gh-repo.png 295w,\n/static/872c00cd4df59382238edfddf5c08859/799d3/del-gh-repo.png 590w,\n/static/872c00cd4df59382238edfddf5c08859/55cb2/del-gh-repo.png 735w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>If you are in doubt, you can <code class=\"language-text\">hide</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">archive</code> it.</p>\n<p>That is it, a simple how to in 5 steps.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to Delete a GitHub Repo","date":"May 19, 2020","description":""}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/delete-gh-repo/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/pseudocode/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How I Write my Pseudocode"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/confirm-ending/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to Solve \"Confirm the Ending\" Algorithm"}}}}}